definition: to wrap up/to bind up/bundle/parcel/package/CL:個|个[ge4]
to cover/to wrap/to hold/to include/to take charge of/to contract (to or for)/package/wrapper/container/bag/to hold or embrace/bundle/packet/CL:個|个[ge4],隻|只[zhi1]

pinyin: Lian2 he2 Bao1 guo3 Fu2 wu4 Gong1 si1

sentences.english: But sometimes DHL they will diverge parcel inspection, then their own packaging.
sentences.chinese: 但有時DHL他們會岔開包裹檢查，然後自己包裝。

sentences.english: There're many ecial rules for mailing packages regarding size and how they're packed.
sentences.chinese: 是的，包裹的大小和包裝法有許多特殊的規定。

sentences.english: People walked through the streets aimlessly with nowhere to go, carrying the few bags and possessions they had left.
sentences.chinese: 人們帶着僅剩的財物包裹漫無目的遊蕩。

sentences.english: After receiving the notice, we will provide you with relevant formalities.
sentences.chinese: 收到包裹單後，我們將爲您辦理相關手續。

sentences.english: In the Most Holy Place he made a pair of sculptured cherubim and overlaid them with gold.
sentences.chinese: 在至聖所按造像的法子造兩個基路伯，用金子包裹。

sentences.english: I went over to hold Eden. The stripes on her blanket were green.
sentences.chinese: 我上前抱住了伊甸，包裹她的小毯子是白底綠紋的。

sentences.english: We received a parcel wrapped in brown paper.
sentences.chinese: 我們收到一個用棕色紙包裝的包裹。

sentences.english: These ones were very similar to Xiao Lung Bao in that there was a delicious soup inside.
sentences.chinese: 跟小籠包一樣，生煎包裏也包裹着香濃又美味的湯。

sentences.english: Non-sew roll, which is warped with wearable rubber, with dynamitic balance adjustment .
sentences.chinese: 無縫管，包裹耐磨橡膠，並做動平衡校正。

sentences.english: And in the most holy house he made two cherubims of image work, and overlaid them with gold.
sentences.chinese: 在至聖所按造像的法子造兩個基路伯，用金子包裹。

sentences.english: This is in real life and you can't have addons sort out the mess for you.
sentences.chinese: 這是現實生活，沒有插件幫你清理包裹。

sentences.english: The long cloak she was wearing enveloped her completely.
sentences.chinese: 她穿着的斗篷把她全包裹起來了。

sentences.english: Any parcel over the dimension limit should be repacked into smaller ones.
sentences.chinese: 超過最大尺寸限度的包裹應分成若干小件。

sentences.english: A: Do you want to register the parcel?
He spent two hours mugging up the statistics before briefing the press.
sentences.chinese: 他花了兩個小時用繩捆紮所有這些包裹。

definition: to stuff full/to cram in/packed tight/chock full
